<br>
You have the kiter, who is someone who can hold kite and spam the mob with massive taunt spells, and then you have the damage dealers, who are usually melee or pets but can include any damage dealing class as well.<br>
<br>
Common aggro kiters (main taunt method) - Wizard (TFlux Staff), Druid (Flame Lick), Ranger (Flame Lick)<br>
<br>
Common damage dealers: Rogue, Monk, Ranger, Warrior, Mage, Necro, Beastlord<br>
<br>
This allows for groups like Ranger+Rogue and other odd combos.<br>
<br>
Also Enchanter + Ranger lets you Fear kite non animals. <p>Caffron, Wizard of &lt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/bsanctuslumen" target="top">Sanctus Lumen</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&gt;, the Good team PK guild.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=invectus>Invectus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/23/03 6:52 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: unconventional, yet effective, groups</span><hr size=1> In Nadox, I had a successful 4 hour session the other night with this group, pulling the shrine:<br>
