<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=445067"TARGET=_blank>Vec gear</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fenwig>Fenwig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 10:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: unconventional, yet effective, groups</span><hr size=1> It's real good to see Wizards all over dealing with the misconceptions.   Like others have mentioned before, I often grab the lfgs either inside guild or out and go from there.  There are so many different tactics that can be used, but they require creativity and work.<br>
<br>
A three-legged monkey could grab a trinity group and be relatively successful.  But it takes a player that knows their role, and knows the role of the other classes present to make a &quot;non-traditional&quot; group work.<br>
<br>
Excellent work! <p>Fenwig Neehighnooker<br>
Sorcerer / Pimp Daddy<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.carolina.rr.com/fenwig/images/chicksdigme2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vannaeluea>VannaEluea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/26/03 5:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: unconventional, yet effective, groups</span><hr size=1> Three Wizards<br>
One SK<br>
One Pally<br>
<br>
All between 40-47 level in the Dreadlands on Cazic-Thule with no C1, C2 or C3 for anyone.  Pally was the main healer, SK the tank.  Group was very stable and lasted a few hours before replacing the Pally and SK with a cleric, beastlord and monk.<br>
<br>
I definitely had more fun switching roles around with the Pally as healer than in the usual level-grind group-- One wizzy would slow, we'd wait for the pally and sk to knock the mob around til about 85%, then all unleash.  Mob would usually turn, and then the Pally and sk did the beat down, while wizzys med.  <br>
<br>
None of us ever got above 20% mana before the next pull, but we all enjoyed, no one died, no one even got close (though the Pally and SK did get pretty banged up).<br>
<br>
Frater Khephra <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showMessageRange?topicID=312.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showPrevMessage?topicID=312.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showNextMessage?topicID=312.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.emailToFriend?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.threadControl?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=312.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graff